  "prompt": "How long can white wine last after it has been open?",
  "response": "Once opened, white wine typically lasts for **3 to 5 days** when stored properly. To maximize its shelf life:\n\n1. **Refrigerate it**: Keep the wine in the fridge to slow down oxidation and preserve its flavor.\n2. **Recork or seal it tightly**: Use the original cork or a wine stopper to minimize exposure to air.\n3. **Store upright**: This reduces the surface area exposed to air.\n\nHowever, the exact duration depends on the type of white wine. Light, crisp wines like Sauvignon Blanc or Pinot Grigio may lose their freshness sooner, while fuller-bodied whites like Chardonnay with more oak aging might last a bit longer. Always use your senses (smell and taste) to check if the wine is still enjoyable. If it smells or tastes off (vinegary or flat), it\u2019s best to discard it.",
